Medium: Ink on paper mounted to board
Additional information:

responsibilities for coloring
AARON generated the drawing and then Cohen painted the colors
on the reverse side of the panel 
Reverse was re-painted over in black at a later date
One of the final works Cohen ever mounted on panel

in a Botanical Garden"
This proccess period can also be referred to as "Jungle"

Additional information:
1983-LATT-Style-H

Notes: The signed Suite was drawn by Harold Cohens Aaron Drawing Machine. These works were drawn at the Tate Museum during the Harold Cohen 1983 exhibition at the Tate. This was the 3rd tour stop for the Aaron Drawing Machine. The first was De Cordova Museum LincolnMassachusetts in 1982. Aaron was then demonstrated at The Brooklyn Museum before traveling to The Tate. After The Tate, Aaron was demonstrated at Arnolfini.There are 9 signed drawings in the suite and they are named, Style A, Style B through Style I.
